HOW WE COLLECT YOUR PERSONAL DATA
Personal data you provide us directly.
We may collect personal data that you directly provide us while using the Services or include it in an email, or other messages that you send us. Such kind of personal data collection would happen during usual business processes.
This personal data may include Player Data and Identifiers, Email, Password, additional data provided by the player, data from the player’s social network profile, Age.
Personal data we collect automatically.
We may automatically collect personal data when you use the Services.
Such personal data may include Player Data and Identifiers, Device Data, Game Data, Location Data, Crash Data.
Personal data we collect from our third parties and partners.
We may receive your personal data from third-party sources and combine it with the personal data we receive directly from you. For example:
advertisers and analytical partners,
We may receive your Device Data on the performance of our apps from our analytical partners and combine it with the information we receive directly from you. We may also receive your advertising IDs from our advertisers if you have agreed to provide them with your advertising IDs.
authentication partners,
We may receive your personal data from a third party to create your account on our Services, when you log in to our Services using third-party credentials.
publishing platforms,
We also receive your personal data from the app stores where our Services are published.
social networking service,
We may receive your personal data from the social networking service such as your social network ID, name/ nickname, photo profile/ image profile, email, friends list, or other information when you play our games,
or access any part of our Service
on the social networking service. The personal data we receive from the social networking service depends on your privacy settings on that social network.
Generated personal data.
We can also generate new data about you by computing and generating the personal data we have. Such personal data may include Payment Data, Identifiers (user ID), Game Data.
CHILDREN’S PRIVACY
Our Services are not directed to those under the age of majority, however, we are committed to protecting the privacy and safety of all our players, including children. Having said that, we do not intentionally or knowingly collect personal data from children. Nevertheless, we do recognize the importance of complying with the age of requirements which vary from country to country.
We encourage parents to educate their children on safe and responsible internet use, and to contact us if they have any concerns about their child’s data collection, usage, or storage. We understand the importance of parental control over their children’s online activities, and we respect parents’ rights to manage and delete their children’s data. If you become aware that we have unintentionally collected personal data from your child, please do not hesitate to contact us, and we will make all reasonable efforts to stop processing such data and erase it as soon as possible.
AUTOMATED DECISIONS/ PROFILING
We neither use automated decision-making nor engage in profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects. Nevertheless, we may utilize your Game and Payments Data to categorize you as a player and generate a group offer for players within that same category.
HOW WE PROTECT YOUR DATA
We maintain appropriate administrative, technical and physical security measures to protect your personal data from accidental, unlawful, or unauthorized destruction, loss, alteration, access, disclosure, or use and other unlawful forms of processing.
We can also anonymize your personal data as soon as we do not need it anymore. Anonymisation is the process of removing personal identifiers, both direct and indirect, that may lead to an individual being identified. The result of this process is anonymous data that cannot be associated with any individual.
HOW LONG DO WE STORE YOUR PERSONAL DATA
Personal data will be kept only for the time needed to achieve the purposes for which it is processed, unless we have a legal right or obligation to retain your data as necessary for our legitimate business interests, such as to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.
We delete your personal data which we process for the performance of the agreement or based on your consent in case you terminate your agreement with us, withdraw your consent, or where you request to remove your personal data, as described in this Privacy Notice.
We may also periodically de-identify unused player data, and we may regularly check and de-identify unnecessary data.
WITH WHOM WE SHARE YOUR PERSONAL DATA
The list of our current third parties and partners are available
here.
Advertising and analytics partners.
We may use analytics services to collect analytical data, and evaluate the usage of our apps, and improve it and make them more appealing to you as a player.
We use advertising services to facilitate the sharing of information that may be relevant, or interesting to you, such as allowing you to earn rewards for viewing in-game ads.
Customer service platforms.
This type of platforms allows us to manage support and contact requests received via email, or by other means, such as the contact form.
Law enforcement or government bodies.
In order to combat fraud and illegal activity, situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person or as required by law, we may process and disclose data with law enforcement or government bodies in response to lawful requests.
Other players.
If you play or register through a social networking service, other players may see your profile data (name and photo), descriptions of your game activity, and read the messages you have posted. If you use our game in response to an invitation from another player, that player may see certain information about your game activity.
Payment services.
We may share payment data with our payment services that process payment transactions or provide other financial services, and for fraud prevention.
We do not and will not collect or process any information related to your payment instruments, such as your credit card number, its expiration date, or your name as written on your card.
Service providers and partner organizations.
We may share your personal data with our service providers as their respective technical solutions may form an integral part of the Services. We also may share your personal data between and among our affiliated companies.
Standard Contractual Clauses are used to share your personal data to ensure that they are properly protected.
INTERNATIONAL TRANSFERS OF PERSONAL DATA
Our Service is global, and your personal data can therefore be transferred to anywhere in the world. We apply the Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission or other appropriate means as legal mechanisms for any such transfer, and make sure that such transfers occur only if there are adequate safeguards in place.
Please note that laws vary from jurisdiction to jurisdiction, so the privacy laws applicable to the places where personal data is transferred to or stored, used, or processed in, may be different from the privacy laws in the country of your residence. By using our Services or providing us with any information through them, you acknowledge such transfer, processing, and storage of your personal data in countries in which privacy regulations may not be as comprehensive as those in the country of your residence.
YOUR RIGHTS
You have certain rights in connection with your personal data and how we handle it.
RIGHTS UNDER THE GDPR
To ensure a swift response, we advise you to contact us through the support features available in our Services if you have any questions regarding data protection or require assistance with resolving issues related to your personal data. Alternatively, you may contact us via email at:
privacy@vizor-apps.com
.
Right to access your personal data.
Under art. 15 of the GDPR, you have a right of access that gives you the right to obtain a copy of your personal data, as well as other supplementary information. It helps to understand how and why we are using your personal data, and check the lawfulness of the processing.
Right to rectify (correct) your personal data.
Under art. 16 of the GDPR, you have the right to have inaccurate personal data rectified. You may also be able to have incomplete personal data completed, although this will depend on the purposes for processing.
Right to have your personal data erased (deleted).
Under art. 17 of the GDPR, you have the right to have personal data erased. This is also known as the ‘right to be forgotten’. The right is not absolute and only applies in certain circumstances.
Right to restrict processing of your personal data.
Art. 18 of the GDPR gives you the right to restrict the processing of your personal data in certain circumstances. This means that you can limit the way that we use your data. This is an alternative to requesting the erasure of your data.
Right to transmit your personal data.
Under art. 20 of the GDPR, you have the right to data portability that gives you the right to receive personal data you have provided to us in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format. It also gives you the right to request that we transmit those data directly to another controller.
Right to object to processing of your personal data.
Art. 21 of the GDPR gives you the right to object to the processing of your personal data at any time. This effectively allows you to stop or prevent us from processing your personal data.
Right to withdraw your consent for personal data processing.
Art. 7 (3) of the GDPR gives you the right to withdraw your consent for personal data processing. Any withdrawal of consent does not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.
Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.
In accordance with art. 77 of the GDPR, you, as a data subject, have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, in particular in the Member State of your habitual residence, place of work, or where an alleged infringement of the GDPR has taken place.
